file=Cybersecurity/warden/custom/security-exception-process/assets/exception-register-template.md · ser:Security Exception Register — [business name]=> Append-only. Every exception: compensating control + hard expiry + residual-risk owner. Expiry fails closed (reverts to policy). Open-exception count is a risk signal.\n · tb=\| ID \| Policy/control excepted \| Reason \| Compensating control \| Expiry (hard) \| Residual risk (register ref) \| Owner \| Approval (warden-low / board-high) \| State \| · tb=\|---\|---\|---\|---\|---\|---\|---\|---\|---\| · tb=\| E-001 \| <FILL_IN> \| \| [required] \| [date] \| [R-ref] \| \| \| open / expired→reverted / renewed-[date] \| · s:Signals=- Open exception count: ___ (rising = policy misfit or discipline slip → warden + operator)\n- Exceptions clustered on one control: ___ → revise that policy\n- Any expired-but-not-reverted: **incident** (fail-closed breach)\n